### Steps to reproduce

The callback of `PopupMenuButton` don't work if there is an `Unique Key`.
It was working perfectly on the last version of `Flutter 3.24.5`.

Clone or run the following **example code** issue bug: https://github.com/marcellocamara/issues/tree/master/Flutter3PopupMenuButton

Removing this line `key: UniqueKey()`, the bug is fixed, allowing the `Second Page` be called normally from user click interaction event callback: 
https://github.com/marcellocamara/issues/blob/master/Flutter3PopupMenuButton/lib/main.dart#L37

This bug is only on `Flutter 3.27`. It works normally, with the `Unique Key`, at `Flutter 3.25`. I'm using a list on the real scenario. I added this unique key at Center widget just to exemplify.

### Expected results

Callback works normally, opening the `Second Page` present on **example code**.

### Actual results

Callback don't work, making it impossible to go to the `Second Page` present on **example code**.

