### Use case

Native apps that use default iOS navigation allow a long-press gesture on the back button to show a list of views in the history stack. The user can drag their finger to a specific view to pop to it with haptic feedback between items.

Examples found in most built-in apps such as Notes, Calendar and Mail but can also be seen in third-party apps that use the normal navigation push/pop structure and app bar. Screen recording of Example in the calendar app recorded on an iPhone 15 Pro Max on iOS 18.2:

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a10c7e28-cf26-41c3-b49c-5ff3b85e2887

